;Arcana Tower
;
; Current tower script, w/central stairs
; restricted stair access
; 
;
VARIABLE PCOLUMN
;
; I# 936 Plant
INUMBER 936
NAME 540
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 3
HIDDEN
;
; I# 941 Amulet, Arcana
INUMBER 941
NAME 4
WORN_NECK
IFPREVERB STEAL -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N gazes about nervously for a moment, then reaches out to swipe %a.
  ECHO OTHERS %A suddenly bursts into eldritch flames, engulfing %i!
  DAMAGEPLR BURN 3000 You are suddenly engulfed in a fiery explosion!
  GMMSG %n just tried to steal %a :)
  REMOVEITEM -1
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GET -1
  IFVAR ORG ! 2
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER As you pick it up, the amulet seems to grow warm and lose its shape. It dissolves into mystical light, drips from your hands and reforms as the droplets hit the ground.
    ECHO OTHERS %N begins to pick up %a, but it seems to dissolve into droplets of mystical light which roll away from his fingers.
    ECHO OTHERS The amulet reforms as the droplets hit the ground.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TOUCH -1
  IFVAR ITEMADJ1 = 145
    IFVAR ORG = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER As you grasp the amulet, you feel its warmth seep into your hand.
      ECHO OTHERS %A glows brightly for a moment as %N grasps it.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LIGHT -1
  CLEARVERB
  ADD ITEMVAL1 1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You touch the amulet with flame; suddenly it begins to glow brightly.
    ECHO OTHERS %N applies flame to %a, which begins to glow brightly.
    EQUAL ITEMADJ1 145
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 1
    ECHO OTHERS As %N applies flame to %a, it liquefies and seeps into the ground.
    ECHO PLAYER As you heat the amulet, it liquefies and seeps into the ground.
    REMOVEITEM -1
    GMMSG %N has just destroyed a Silver Arcana amulet.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 0
    GMMSG The item %N has just looked at is an uninitialized Silver Arcana Amulet. Its VAL2 is currently 0.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMADJ1 ! 145
    ECHO PLAYER You see nothing extraodrinary.
  ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You see an intricately molded crystal amulet shaped like an owl. The image
      ECHO PLAYER reminds you that an initiate of the Order of the Silver Arcana has a duty to
      ECHO PLAYER gain knowledge and keep the lore and the Light.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You see an intricately molded crystal amulet shaped like a griffin in flight.
      ECHO PLAYER The image reminds you that a journeyman of the Order of the Silver Arcana
      ECHO PLAYER must strive to improve his or her skills in a responsible manner.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You see at an intricately molded amulet of a pegasus in flight. It is made of
      ECHO PLAYER a pure blue-white crystal, reminding you that as a master of the Order of the
      ECHO PLAYER Silver Arcana, you have a selfless duty to preserve magic throughout the
      ECHO PLAYER Realms, increase the knowledge of the Arcana, and keep the Light.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 4
      ECHO PLAYER You look at an intricately molded amulet shaped into the form of a Dragon in
      ECHO PLAYER flight. Ready to pounce on its prey, it reminds you that a High Master of the
      ECHO PLAYER Order of the Silver Arcana must temper his or her powers with the wisdom
      ECHO PLAYER gained through training, and keep the Light with the knowledge that things
      ECHO PLAYER are not always black and white.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 0
    GMMSG The item %N has just looked at is an uninitialized Silver Arcana Amulet. Its VAL2 is currently 0.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMADJ1 ! 145
    ECHO PLAYER You see nothing extraodrinary.
  ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze at an amulet carved in the shape of a huge owl in flight.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze at an amulet carved in the shape of a feathery Griffin in flight.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze at an amulet carved in the shape of a pegasus in flight.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 4
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze at an amulet carved in the shape of a wise old dragon in flight.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER As you twist and turn the amulet, light plays around it.
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 1
    ECHO OTHERS As %n brings %h hand up to %h amulet, %s shimmers with a soft aura of energy.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 2
    ECHO OTHERS %N turns %a and begins to radiate a soft, shifting light.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 3
    ECHO OTHERS %N's form shimmers with mystical power.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 4
    ECHO OTHERS %N's form seems to shift and shimmer, casting off a mystical light.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
  IFVAR ITEMADJ1 ! 145
    ECHO PLAYER Nothing happens.
  ELSE
    IFVAR ORG = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You focus upon the amulet and it shimmers...
      IFVAR ORGRANK < 50
        EQUAL ITEMADJ2 152
        EQUAL ITEMVAL2 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ORGRANK > 49
        IFVAR ORGRANK < 100
          EQUAL ITEMADJ2 358
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 2
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ORGRANK > 99
        IFVAR ORGRANK < 200
          EQUAL ITEMADJ2 347
          EQUAL ITEMVAL2 3
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ORGRANK > 199
        EQUAL ITEMADJ2 225
        EQUAL ITEMVAL2 4
      ENDIF
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER ...a few moments later %a solidifies before your eyes.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;                       Arcana tower Room descriptions start here  
;
; R# 341 : Silver Arcana, Reception
NUMBER 341
NAME Silver Arcana, Reception
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The floorboards of the reception area have been worn smooth by the passage 
of many feet. At the center is a pile of smooth stone blocks. On the north
wall are three exits leading deeper into the tower. The western-most exit
is a polished oaken door, while the eastern-most exit is an arch filled with
glowing swirls of fog. The frame of the arch is carved with runes and seems
to radiate power. A crystal pillar rises from the floor up into the center
of the tower, surrounded by the floating blocks of a spiral staircase. The
central exit leads to what appears to be a shop of some kind, while an 
opening in the south wall leads back to the street. You see a desk against
the west wall with a large book resting on it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 487
EXIT O 251
EXIT U 2503
; Desk
ITEM 0 201
; Book
ITEM 1 423
; Polished oaken door
ITEM 2 65 ADJ1=241 ADJ2=447 VAL1=0 VAL2=488 OPEN UNLOCKED
; Rune carved Arch
ITEM 3 60 ADJ1=1322 ADJ2=46 VAL2=343
EXTEND 3 filled with glowing swirls of fog
; Crystal pillar
ITEM 4 1700 ADJ1=77
EXTEND 4 which is the center of a floating spiral staircase
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
;
IFPREVERB UP -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    IFVAR ORG ! 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You attempt to climb the stairs, but your foot is stopped by an unseen force.
      ECHO OTHERS You see %N walk to the spiral stairs but stop with one foot poised above the first stair.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER There is a guest book resting on one corner next to depressions that seem to have, at one time, held quill and ink.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The book contains pages of signatures including those of past Masters of the Arcana such as Yshtarin and Dagmar.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 2
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    IFVAR ORG ! 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You attempt to go through the door, but an unseen force pushes you back.
      ECHO OTHERS You see %N step up to the door to the northwest and then stop suddenly.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;               Archway is NOT powered by the tower power source.
IFPREVERB LOOK 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You see a shimmering wall of fog before you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 3
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO GROUP You step through the arch and into the observatory.
    MOVEGROUP 343
  ELSE
    IFVAR ORG = 2
      AFFECT 343
      ECHO ALL The air in front of the arch shimmers for a moment and %P appears.
      AFFECT 341
      ECHO GROUP You step through the arch and into the fog. %cAfter a few moments of disorientation, you find yourself standing in the observatory.
      ECHO OTHERS You watch %P step through the arch and disappear into the glowing fog.
      MOVEGROUP 343
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You attempt to go through the arch, but the fog becomes solid and stops you.
      ECHO OTHERS You see %N attempt to step through the fog, but %s bounces back as if hitting a wall.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
; R# 343 : Silver Arcana, Observatory
NUMBER 343
NAME Silver Arcana, Observatory
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself within a glass enclosed room, which allows you to look down
upon all of Fayd and the surrounding countryside. Looking up provides you with
an uninterrupted view of the heavens above the tower. The chamber also contains
a small bookcase along one wall and a number of arcane devices resting upon a
table. Inset into the south wall is a rune carved arch filled with glowing 
swirls of fog. The center of the room is taken up by a large table that glows
with controlled power. The immense elkyri base supports a top of diamontine
upon which rests a glittering plate made up entirely of creod. Seventeen gems
pulsate in sequence to the heartbeat of the tower, each changing the flow of
energy as it passes by. The very air around it crackles with the power of this
device.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; glass window
ITEM 0 249 ADJ1=143
; rune carved arch
ITEM 1 60 ADJ1=1322 ADJ2=46 VAL2=343
EXTEND 1 filled with glowing swirls of fog
; Small Bookcase
ITEM 2 1028 ADJ1=294
; Pedestal
ITEM 3 292 ADJ3=145
EXTEND 3 that pulsates with an inner power
; Small Platform
ITEM 4 365 ADJ1=294
EXTEND 4 next to the pedestal
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
You see numerous diamonds and precious gems set into the bed of
creod that makes up the top surface of the pedestal. The diamontine
and elkyri that support and cradle the creod are shot through with
streaks of fiery and icy metal.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You see the entire city of Fayd spread out below you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You see a shimmering wall of fog before you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
  CLEARVERB
  AFFECT 341
  ECHO ALL The air in front of the arch shimmers for a moment and %P appears.
  AFFECT 343
  ECHO GROUP You step through the arch and into the fog. %cAfter a few moments of disorientation, you find yourself standing in the reception area.
  ECHO OTHERS You watch %P step through the arch and disappear into the glowing fog.
  MOVEGROUP 341
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SEARCH 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You find numerous texts of an arcane nature.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The platform prevents you from reaching the pedestal.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS As %N gestures at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, surrounding %i and dropping %i to %h knees in agony.
  DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 200 As you gesture at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, surrounding you and dropping you to your knees in agony.%c [Round: 10 sec]
  POSITION LAY
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
  EQUAL MANAPOINTS 0
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PROJECT 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS As %N gestures at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, surrounding %i and dropping %i to %h knees in agony.
  DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 200 As you gesture at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, surrounding you and dropping you to your knees in agony.%c [Round: 10 sec]
  POSITION LAY
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
  EQUAL PSIPOINTS 0
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONC 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS As %N gestures at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, momentarily surrounding %i and dropping %i to %h knees in agony.
  DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 50 As you gesture at the pedestal erratic pulsations of magical energy surge forth, momentarily surrounding you and dropping you to your knees in agony.%c [Round: 10 sec]
  POSITION LAY
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
  EQUAL PSIPOINTS 0
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 4
  CLEARVERB
  AFFECT 2501
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM ! 0
    AFFECT 343
    ECHO PLAYER There is no room for you on the platform.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
    AFFECT 343
    DISBAND
    ECHO PLAYER You step up onto the platform.
    ECHO OTHERS %N steps up onto the platform.
    MOVE 2501
  ENDIF
ENDIF
