;
; R# 488 : Arcana Tower, Basement 
NUMBER 488
NAME Arcana Tower, Basement
ASTRAL
DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The rusting metallic walls of this room are covered with spider webs and
various insects caught within them. Behind the webs, the northern wall is
covered with graffiti. To the south is a dull blue curtain and a door
sits in the west wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 341
; Curtain
ITEM 0 1031 VAL2=494 ADJ2=29
; Graffiti
ITEM 1 235
; Door
ITEM 2 65 VAL1=0 VAL2=2502 OPEN UNLOCKED
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
;
IFPREVERB GO 0
  ECHO PLAYER You push the curtain out of your way and stride into the initiation chamber.
  ECHO OTHERS %N pushes the curtain out of the way and strides into the initiation chamber.
endif
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear the scurrying of spiders from behind the webs.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 7
    ECHO PLAYER The Tower of the Silver Arcana is the oldest and the tallest building in Fayd. It seems to end here, but you recall reading about the tower's various secret rooms and passages...
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The air smells terribly stale here.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Comments of varying degrees of wit and sobriety compete for space. "Harpies
  ECHO PLAYER suck eggs" is faintly visible beneath, "Sufficiently advanced technology might
  ECHO PLAYER resemble magick, but it'll never match the style." "We love Frumpy!" is
  ECHO PLAYER scribbled in several places.
ENDIF
;
; R# 494 : Initiation chamber
NUMBER 494
NAME Initiation chamber
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
It is difficult to gauge the dimensions of this chamber. The walls are
glassy smooth and reflective and all sound seems dampened in the still
air. Against the far wall is a dull crystal column.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; Column
ITEM 0 1509 adj1=287 adj2=77
; Curtain
ITEM 1 1031 VAL2=488
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
;
IFPREVERB TOUCH 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO OTHERS %N touches the column for a moment.
  ECHO PLAYER You rest your palms against the column and you can feel faint flickers of power beneath them.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER Your mind feels the brief touch of some presence.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL A voice rings from the air, "If you are hearing this, then something has gone seriously wrong."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The voice continues, "This message is only to be heard if the powersource of the tower has shut down."
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL "In order to reactivate the column consult%c"Galdwin Magicbane's Compleate Reference and Resource Guide to the Magical Aspects of Creod"%cwhich is stored in the tower observatory."
ENDIF
