*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls of this large room are rough hewn from the bedrock below the tower.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; Door
ITEM 0 65 VAL1=0 VAL2=488 OPEN UNLOCKED
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
;
; R# 2500 : Path of Statues
NUMBER 2500
NAME Path of Statues
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Gently swaying branches hang over the path, casting a pleasant shade over
the walk during the heat of daytime. Two statues, both set back amongst
the trees, add a pleasant sculptured view to the setting. The walkway
meanders outward, and ends, at the beginning of the cultivated farmlands
of the Gilnaerd family.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;EXIT N 2501
EXIT O 544
ITEM 0 346
EXTEND 0 of King Frederick the I
ITEM 1 346
EXTEND 1 of Yvorin
; Ucantsee
ITEM 9 693
;
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The statue is an amateurish portrayal of King Frderick the I, gazing out
over the horizon, a brilliant greatsword held at the ready.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Yvorin, former Guildmaster of the Silver Arcana, has been sculpted to
portray his studious demeanor and his kindness.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
; R# 2501 : Arcana Observatory, Platform
NUMBER 2501
NAME Arcana Observatory, Platform
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing upon the platform you can see more clearly the settings on the pedestal.
Aquamarine and tourmaline, garnet and pearl, emerald and ruby, sapphire and 
moonstone, each setting is between the settings holding the phase diamonds.
The gems all pulsate with inner life and surround you with their glow.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 343
